            <title>[SPARK-31014] InMemoryStore: CountingRemoveIfForEach misses to remove key from parentToChildrenMap</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-31014</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-30964&quot; title=&quot;Accelerate InMemoryStore with a new index&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-30964&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-30964&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces the secondary index which defines the relationship between parent - children and able to operate all children for given parent faster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This change is not applied to&#160;CountingRemoveIfForEach, so there&apos;s a chance &quot;countingRemoveAllByIndexValues&quot; missed to remove key&#160;from parentToChildrenMap.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
